##I haven't been to key areas in over 40 days. Why are we quarantined? They said: Because Your ID CARD is Wuhan!

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

They looked at my phone, they looked at my health certificate, but no matter how I explained it, they said I needed to go to a central quarantine point.

Dictation | Mr. Zhao

Arrangement | Huang Qi

I made all the preparations, March 5 from my hometown in Guizhou, to Guangxi to resume work, Surprise, to Guangxi, but was as "key epidemic area personnel. ".

At the moment, I am quarantined in the hotel, I asked them: I have not been to the key areas in the last 40 days, why do you need isolation? They said, because your ID card is from Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The company's project resumed production and bidding to wait for me to promote, the original plan to go to Hainan, Guangdong and other places, but now, I can't go anywhere. I was appealing to all sides, and four days later, no one told me why I was not allowed to go out.

The three of US went back to work, and I was the only one in quarantine

I'm the executive director of an Environmental Technology Company, headquartered in Wuhan, with projects all over the country. I usually work in Wuhan most of the time. When I went to university, my Hukou was transferred to the school. Ten years ago, when I graduated from university, my Hukou was changed to Wuhan Identity Card.

On January 19, the Spring Festival holiday, I returned from Wuhan to the Rural Village of Majiang County in Guizhou Province for the Chinese New Year.

Back home, I learned from the news that the new crown pneumonia epidemic in Wuhan is serious. As a precaution, I hardly left the house as soon as I got home. On January 24, government workers came to my house and asked me to stay put. I didn't go out.

Throughout the Spring Festival, I have been following the development of the epidemic. In my circle of friends, I post news and news about the new crown disease. Every day, watching the data of confirmed patients, watching the prevention and control measures around the country, watching the doctors to rescue, ups and downs.

Until the late February, finally saw the dawn, Wuhan epidemic slowly has eased the appearance of the resumption of work has hope.

In late February, the media began to report on how to do a good job to resume production, we contacted the Guangxi side of the business partners, the project to start, the partners need us to go.

I know it's an emergency, so try to be prepared. One of my colleagues from my hometown in Chongqing had arrived in Guangxi more than half a month early for the Spring Festival. I asked him what local requirements were for people from other places to enter. Colleagues say, as long as it is not from the key areas, there is no special procedures. After he arrived in Guangxi from Chongqing, everything was normal and he could work.

According to the request of my hometown in Guizhou Province, on March 2, I went to the village committee for registration and then went to the Township Health Center for a physical examination. I got the health application certificate for migrant workers from Majiang County. The whole process was in accordance with the requirements. The certificate clearly states, in the last month, whether I have a fever, have recently been to the focus of the epidemic areas, have had contact with patients and so on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On March 5, I was driving from my home when I picked up two colleagues at Kaili South Station, one in Chongqing and the other in Changsha.

Over 600 kilometers, we drove for over seven hours. All the way is very smooth, the highway has no epidemic prevention and control checkpoints, we walk all the way to the end, more than nine o'clock at night to reach the town of Wu Wei, Nanning City, Guangxi. After a night's rest, he set off the next morning at around 7:00 a.m. and went to live in changling community in Shangsi County, Guangxi at around 9:00 p.m.

On March 7, my colleagues and I went to the Partner Company to inspect the situation and make arrangements for the resumption of work and production.

Everything seems to be going well. My mind is full of things on the project. After Guangxi, I have to rush to deal with the resumption of work on other projects.

But everything changed on the afternoon of March 7.

That afternoon, the community workers came to me and my colleagues and asked us to go to the community to register the migrants. Later I know, is the community to see my license plate is Hubei, reported to the community.

I think this is also right, we are very cooperative to fill out the relevant form documents, the evening police station, the local government departments to verify the call many times.

To our surprise, after we reported all the information truthfully, they came to the conclusion that they were going to take me to a central quarantine point, where my colleagues wouldn't have to go.

When I asked them why I needed to be quarantined, I was told that my ID card was from Hubei Province.

For the next hour or so, I kept explaining to the deputy mayor in charge of the epidemic, the relevant person in charge of the police station, the community director, the person in charge of the quarantine point, I showed them my health certificate, let them use my cell phone number to check my whereabouts for more than a month before, I told them that I am the head of the company, the recent business trip to promote the resumption of production..

There was no conflict because I was the head of the company, and I felt that the matter was always clarified, and that I could not be forcibly isolated if I did not conform to the rules. And I recorded it, and I said, "If you don't follow the rules, you will be held accountable. ". The staff said it was okay to record.

I followed them to the quarantine hotel, where I figured I'd keep looking for the authorities, and we'd figure it out.

No one gets to decide how to get me out

With the help of the project partners, I called the head of the local Bureau of Industry and information, the head of the Sugar Bureau (our joint venture is in the sugar industry) , and the head of the cultural and tourism bureau, because the management of the isolation points is under the jurisdiction of the cultural and tourism bureau.

I told my story, and the leaders said that they would report my story to the local command for the prevention and control of new pneumonia, and they told me to wait for an answer, and then there was no answer.

I've also left three messages on the State Department's Web site about the outbreak.

I'm staying at the Quarantine Point Hotel, and I can't go anywhere, so all I can do is keep trying to find out who's in charge of me: I'm being quarantined just because of my Wuhan ID card.

I've spent the last few days trying to reach out to all sorts of people, but all I've heard from them is: no one can decide to lift my quarantine.

Now I am in an awkward position. I got the health code on the official "Guangxi Health Code" , which is shown as green, meaning I can move freely in Guangxi. In other words, the decision to isolate me was a mistake, but no one corrected the obvious mistake.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the morning of March 10, I got the phone number of a deputy director of the Guangxi Shangsi County epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters, surnamed Huang, and I texted him. I explained my situation once again. I told him that I was the head of an enterprise. My enterprise operates in Hubei, Hunan, Guangxi, Guangdong, Hainan and other provinces. It is actively promoting the resumption of work and production, i don't think it's protocol to isolate me, and I'd like command to investigate. I got a reply that afternoon. He said command had done some research and decided I should remain in quarantine.

In the afternoon of March 10, I reported my situation through the 12345. The hotline made an urgent treatment for me. That night, the Ministry of Culture and Tourism, the Ministry of Industry and information, the CDC and other departments all contacted me to verify the situation, as hard as it is for them, where does the long road of investigation end?

Am I at risk of contracting a disease if I am not from a priority area and am now isolated from people who are actually from a priority area? I hope command will consider it for me.
